Subject: Default install.ps1 $Branch to "release" for argo customers

The Windows PowerShell installer declares `[string]$Branch = "main"` and clones
that branch (`git clone --branch $Branch`, with a ZIP fallback on
`refs/heads/$Branch.zip`). On the argo fork `main` is the workshop layout
(upstream/, patches/, overlay/, rename engine — NOT a runnable install); the
customer-runnable rebranded tree lives only on `release`. So a Windows customer
running the documented `iex (irm .../install.ps1)` installs the dev workshop and
ends up with a tree where the `argo` package is not importable/runnable.

This is the exact bug patch 0006 fixed for the bash install.sh (BRANCH
main->release); the equivalent Windows fix was never written. The `-Branch`
override is intact (developers can still pass `-Branch main`). IU-FR-7, IU-AC-4.

--- a/scripts/install.ps1
+++ b/scripts/install.ps1
@@ -15,7 +15,7 @@
 param(
     [switch]$NoVenv,
     [switch]$SkipSetup,
-    [string]$Branch = "main",
+    [string]$Branch = "release",
     # -Commit and -Tag are higher-precedence variants of -Branch for users
     # who need reproducible installs (desktop installer pinning, CI, release
     # bundles).  When set, the repository stage clones $Branch (faster than
